  "prompt": "What is FARC?",
  "response": "FARC, or the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (Fuerzas Armadas Revolucionarias de Colombia), is a guerrilla movement that originated in Colombia in 1964. It was initially established as the armed wing of the Colombian Communist Party with the goal of representing the rural poor by promoting agrarianism and resisting perceived imperialism and government oppression. Over the years, FARC became one of the largest and most influential insurgent groups in Colombia, engaging in various forms of warfare, including guerrilla tactics, kidnappings, and narcotics trafficking, to fund its operations.\n\nIn recent years, particularly in 2016, FARC reached a peace agreement with the Colombian government. This agreement involved FARC transitioning from an armed group into a political party known as the Common Alternative Revolutionary Force (maintaining the FARC acronym), and many of its members were integrated into civilian life. This marked a significant milestone in Colombia's efforts to end decades of internal conflict. Despite the peace agreement, some factions and splinter groups chose not to demobilize and continue their insurgency, posing ongoing challenges for the country.",
